\cf2 Other sample rates and word lengths have not been assessed or accommodated as they are not common in practical audio applications. Double and quad speed modes have not been assessed as they require significantly higher clock speeds and overall data rates.\
There are two common I2S serial audio synchronisation modes:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 STD	Phillips or I2S standard. The first BCLK cycle after LRCLK rises is not sampled.  \
LJ	No delay between LRCK rising and first sampled BCLK\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Both modes are synchronised with BCLK falling as LRCLK rises, and data is sampled on the BCLK rising edge.\
